aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104erz1665702688168.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/erz1665702688168.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/erz1665702688168.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"erz1665702688168\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Design the Layout of Reports \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the Report component. You can add header and footer frames to define pages headers and footers, and break frames to control page break behavior.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"erz1665702688168__context_w603ab1b5b1_w604ab1b5_w605ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"erz1665702688168__topic_d24764e1_d24765e1_d24766e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"erz1665702688168__p_d24767e1_d24768e1_d24769e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvl1690356504825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.\">Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"erz1665702688168__topic_d24770e1_d24771e1_d24772e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"erz1665702688168__p_d24773e1_d24774e1_d24775e1\">In Report components, Uniface automatically prints all the retrieved occurrences. It is therefore recommended that you not draw repeating occurrences. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrb1665702688237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrb1665702688237.html\" title=\"Both forms and reports can be used for printing, but report components are the most appropriate choice when you need to provide specialized print control or batch processing. A report component does not allow user interaction or database I/O.\">Design Guidelines for Printing</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"erz1665702688168__li_d12320e1_d12321e1_d12322e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"erz1665702688168__p_d24776e1_d24777e1_d24778e1\">Resize and arrange the entities, fields, and\n               labels on the Canvas to design the layout. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">A field wraps according to the horizontal size of the field as defined in the\n                  report. It is possible to prevent wrapping.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"erz1665702688168__li_d12323e1_d12324e1_d12325e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">You can add labels to the component. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hfa1665702613944.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hfa1665702613944.html\" title=\"Use the Label template to add labels for fields, as well as other text to be displayed on the component.\">Define Labels and Text in Forms and Reports</a>.\n                 </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"erz1665702688168__li_d12326e1_d12327e1_d12328e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"erz1665702688168__p_d24779e1_d24780e1_d24781e1\">To add information at the top and the bottom of\n               the page, define a Header Frame and a Footer Frame. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">To insert column headers, page breaks, or conditional information, define one or\n                  more Break Frames. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"riu1665702611985.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/riu1665702611985.html\" title=\"To add information at the top and the bottom of printed page, define a header frame and a footer frame in a report (or a form used for printing). To conditionally include information in a report, define break frames.\">Define Header, Footer, and Break Frames</a>.\n               </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"erz1665702688168__li_d12329e1_d12330e1_d12331e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"erz1665702688168__p_d24782e1_d24783e1_d24784e1\">Optionally, use area frames to group data in the\n               layout together as a single unit. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ljw1665702610670.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ljw1665702610670.html\" title=\"In reports, area frames can be used to add and protect text as part of an entity in Report components.\">Area Frames for Printing</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"erz1665702688168__li_d12332e1_d12333e1_d12334e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To prevent widows and orphans in a printed frame or occurrence, select an entity or\n               area frame, right-click and choose a <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Printing</span> option, such as\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Frame on Same Page</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Occurrence on\n                  Same Page</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fwo1665702688306.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fwo1665702688306.html\" title=\"Determines how Uniface handles page breaks if there is not enough room to print a complete frame or occurrence.\">Page feed after occurrence</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmx1665702870076.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Reports</a><p>Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrb1665702688237.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Design Guidelines for Printing</a><p>Both forms and reports can be used for printing, but report components are the most appropriate choice when you need to provide specialized print control or batch processing. A report component does not allow user interaction or database I/O.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxs1665702688385.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Layouts for Printing</a><p>The following examples illustrate the effect that the component layout has on the printed output.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyd1665702989016.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Printing from Uniface</a><p>Uniface supports printing from form and report components, which determine the content and layout of the data to be printed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a><p>Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527278\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527278\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Design the Layout of Reports Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Design the Layout of Reports Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the Report component. You can add header and footer frames to define pages headers and footers, and break frames to control page break behavior. For more information, see Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports . In Report components, Uniface automatically prints all the retrieved occurrences. It is therefore recommended that you not draw repeating occurrences. For more information, see Design Guidelines for Printing . Resize and arrange the entities, fields, and labels on the Canvas to design the layout. A field wraps according to the horizontal size of the field as defined in the report. It is possible to prevent wrapping. You can add labels to the component. For more information, see Define Labels and Text in Forms and Reports . To add information at the top and the bottom of the page, define a Header Frame and a Footer Frame. To insert column headers, page breaks, or conditional information, define one or more Break Frames. For more information, see Define Header, Footer, and Break Frames . Optionally, use area frames to group data in the layout together as a single unit. For more information, see Area Frames for Printing . To prevent widows and orphans in a printed frame or occurrence, select an entity or area frame, right-click and choose a Printing option, such as Print Frame on Same Page or Print Occurrence on Same Page . For more information, see Page feed after occurrence . Related Links Reports Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing. Design Guidelines for Printing Both forms and reports can be used for printing, but report components are the most appropriate choice when you need to provide specialized print control or batch processing. A report component does not allow user interaction or database I/O. Layouts for Printing The following examples illustrate the effect that the component layout has on the printed output. Printing from Uniface Uniface supports printing from form and report components, which determine the content and layout of the data to be printed. Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}